===Conjunction===
{{en-con}}

# {{obsolete}} {{non-gloss definition|Introducing a direct [[interrogative]] question (often with correlative {{term|or}}) which indicates doubt between [[alternative]]s.}}
#* '''1526''', William Tyndale, trans. ''Bible'', Mark II:
#*: '''whether''' ys it easyer to saye to the sicke of the palsey, thy synnes ar forgeven the: or to saye, aryse, take uppe thy beed and walke?
#* '''1616''', William Shakespeare, ''King John'', I.i:
#*: '''Whether''' hadst thou rather be a Faulconbridge, [...] Or the reputed sonne of Cordelion?
# {{non-gloss definition|Used to introduce an indirect interrogative question that consists of multiple alternative possibilities (usually with correlative {{term|or}})}}.
#: ''He chose the correct answer, but '''whether''' by luck or by skill I don't know.''
#* {{quote-news
